    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "COU1 parametric sensitivity — material properties and boundary conditions",
    "description": "Cortical and cancellous bone modulus (±20%), titanium alloy yield strength (±5%), and rod-screw interface friction coefficient (0.1–0.4) were independently varied using a one-at-a-time design. Construct stiffness QoI showed greatest sensitivity to titanium modulus (±3.8% response range) and friction coefficient (±2.1%), while yield force was dominated by titanium yield strength variation (±4.6%); all responses remained within the 10% acceptance bound, confirming model robustness to plausible input uncertainty."
  },
